TV hosts Vladimir Solovyov and Nataliya Nikonorova took aim at Foreign Secretary Liz Truss after Aiden Aslin and Shaun Pinner were sentenced to death by a court in the Donetsk People's Republic. Ms Nikonorova said she was surprised Ms Truss had refused to recognise the sentence to which Mr Solovyov responded: "So if something terrible happens and they are executed, they will not recognise their deaths? "Will this bring these people back to life?" Ms Nikonorova went on to say "no-one is helping them". FOLLOW BELOW FOR UPDATES... 